ABAKALIKI – Governor of Bauchi State, Bala Mohammed, said the Peoples Democratic Party was set to take back power from the ruling All Progressives Congress, come 2023. Mr Mohammed who stated this on Friday in Abakaliki,Ebonyi State, when he visited to consult Ebonyi PDP delegates, said the PDP had many eminently qualified presidential Aspirants, capable of taking the Nigeria out of the wood if elected president in 2023. He described APC’s led federal government as an aberration and a huge obstruction to the growth and development of Nigeria. -Advertisement- The presidential hopeful said Nigerians only witnessed democracy during the regimes of former President Olusegun Obasanjo and former President Goodluck Jonathan. He said President Muhammadu Buhari’s regime was characterized with nepotism, discrimination, bad governance, and corruption at its highest level. He said under him as FCT Minister, he solved the problem poor road network, and assured that if given the opportunity to preside over the affairs of Nigeria, he would turn things around positively. “We are coming back to take back power. We have so many candidates in the PDP and we are all eminently qualified to Nigerians the kind of governance they want. But the take away that brought me to Ebonyi is for you to know me, the opportunity to know the country and for you to see me and hear me. In FCT, we reduced the trouble times by bringing good roads. “The APC administration is an aberration, is an obstruction to our growth and development. POLL “Only the years Nigerians knew that there was democracy was during Obasanjo and during Jonathan. Yes, what happen in this regime is nepotism, corruption, discrimination, bad governance, corruption at its highest level,”he said.